{"id":"project-LICHEN-66ys","title":"CoAP parser accepts payload marker followed by empty payload (RFC violation)","description":"File: rust/lichen-coap/src/codec.rs:125-129

The parser accepts messages with a payload marker (0xFF) followed by zero bytes of payload:

    let (options_end, payload_start) = match find_payload_marker(&data[options_start..])? {
        Some(off) => (options_start + off, options_start + off + 1),
        None => (data.len(), data.len()),
    };

RFC 7252 Section 3 states: 'The presence of a marker followed by a zero-length payload MUST be processed as a message format error.'

Example: [0x40, 0x01, 0x00, 0x01, 0xFF] should be rejected but is accepted.

Impact: The parser accepts malformed CoAP messages that other RFC-compliant implementations would reject. This could cause interoperability issues or allow malformed messages to be processed.

Fix: After finding payload marker, verify that payload_start < data.len() or return an error.","status":"open","priority":3,"issue_type":"bug","owner":"me@mark.atwood.name","created_at":"2026-07-12T06:31:25.396867Z","created_by":"Mark Atwood","updated_at":"2026-07-12T06:31:25.396916Z"}

